Patch Set 14:

"Not totally clear why the stripe count is set to zero for released files, but we'll see how this behaves in testing."

This is because I want to keep most of the current code working. If I set released file's stripe count non-zero, I have to change all references of lsm_stripe_count to:

if (pattern & LOV_PATTERN_F_RELEASED)
    stripe_count = 0;
else
    stripe_count = lsm->lsm_stripe_count;

Also I better change the name of lsm_stripe_count to something else to prevent it from being referred directly.

However, GETSTRIPE ioctl will return 0 stripe count for released file, but getstripe and getxattr will return original stripe count.

Patch Set 14:

I have tested v14 with hsm code, it works fine. I have just found a bug hit at layout_swap after restore
diff --git a/lustre/lod/lod_lov.c b/lustre/lod/lod_lov.c
index 0597276..5f6d383 100644
--- a/lustre/lod/lod_lov.c
+++ b/lustre/lod/lod_lov.c
@@ -761,7 +761,7 @@ int lod_get_stripe_count(const struct lu_env *env, const struct lu_buf *buf,

        if (magic != LOV_MAGIC_V1 && magic != LOV_MAGIC_V3)
                RETURN(-EINVAL);
-       if (le32_to_cpu(lmm->lmm_pattern) != LOV_PATTERN_RAID0)
+       if (lov_pattern(le32_to_cpu(lmm->lmm_pattern)) != LOV_PATTERN_RAID0)
                RETURN(-EINVAL);

        *stripe_count = le16_to_cpu(lmm->lmm_stripe_count);
